@Reasoning
Calls are the single most complex MIR node: they sit at the boundary of
the optimizer's reasoning (a call can clobber memory, define new SSA
values, transfer control). Encoding direct vs indirect via a flag (rather
than two distinct opcodes) lets the inliner test eligibility with a single
load and treat callee as either a string-table lookup or an SSA value.

is_tail_call is recorded at construction time because it is decided by the
frontend or by tail-call analysis early in the pipeline; lower passes only
ever clear the flag (when a tail call gets out-of-lined). Storing it here
preserves the decision across all transformations until the LIR layer
finally consumes it for jmp-vs-call selection.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Creates a function call instruction. For direct calls, callee is a function
name string pointer. For indirect calls, callee is a value ID (function pointer).
Arguments are passed as a list of value IDs.
@End Implementation

