@Reasoning
P2-D introduced FFI dispatch through MIR, requiring the LIR lowering pass
to know two facts that are not derivable from the MIR_CALL opcode alone:
whether the target is an external (non-Runa) symbol, and which calling
convention it expects. Storing those two facts directly on the call node
keeps the LIR lowering pass purely local (one node, one decision) and
avoids a side-table lookup keyed by callee.

The is_external bit is distinct from is_indirect because external calls
may still be direct (named C functions) and Runa-internal calls may still
be indirect (function-pointer dispatch). Separating the two preserves all
four combinations cleanly.
@End Reasoning

