@Reasoning
The unconditional jump is the simplest terminator and is deliberately kept
distinct from a degenerate branch (with one target). This separation lets
CFG simplification recognize "single-successor block" by opcode without
having to compare branch targets, and it lets the LIR backend select the
shortest jump encoding for the target distance without rejecting cases
where both branch targets happen to be equal.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Creates an unconditional jump instruction (terminator). Transfers control
directly to target_block_id with no condition check.
@End Implementation

