Atomic operations need a dedicated node because they are opaque to most
optimizations: they cannot be reordered, hoisted out of loops without
proof, or duplicated across paths. Recording memory_order on the node
lets each atomic carry its own ordering constraint instead of forcing
the whole basic block into the strongest order.

